sample_vir_sum <- sum_id %>% 
  filter(species_code == "stop") %>% 
  group_by(site, species, island) %>% 
  summarize(n=n()) %>%
  group_by(species) %>% 
  summarize(n_sites = n(),
            n_total = sum(n),
            n_median = median(n),
            se = sd(n)/sqrt(n_sites))

sample_vet_sum <- sum_id %>% 
  filter(species_code == "qup") %>% 
  group_by(site, species, island) %>% 
  summarize(n=n()) %>%
  group_by(species) %>% 
  summarize(n_sites = n(),
            n_total = sum(n),
            n_median = median(n),
            se = sd(n)/sqrt(n_sites))

Table 1. Variable definitions

Variable Definition Unit
Time spent grazing Proportion of time spent grazing during follow fraction
Bite rate Bite rate while actively Grazing bites/second
Feeding rate Bite rate over total follow time bites/minute
Foray size Number of consecutive bites taken during single grazing foray bites/foray

Testing parametric assumptions

### Normality

hist(sum_id$fr) # positive skew

shapiro.test(sum_id$fr) # non-normal
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  sum_id$fr
## W = 0.92437, p-value = 1.891e-12
hist(sum_id$br) # positive skew

shapiro.test(sum_id$br) # non-normal
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  sum_id$br
## W = 0.96581, p-value = 2.029e-07
hist(sum_id$g_frac) # positive skew

shapiro.test(sum_id$g_frac) # non-normal
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  sum_id$g_frac
## W = 0.96445, p-value = 1.248e-07
hist(sum_id$for_bites) # positive skew

shapiro.test(sum_id$for_bites) # non-normal
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  sum_id$for_bites
## W = 0.80023, p-value < 2.2e-16
# all positively skewed, non-normally distributed -> should use median, should use Kruskall-Wallis

Panel graph of site differences

Kruskal-Wallis tests

vir <- sum_id %>% filter(species_code == "stop")
vet <- sum_id %>% filter(species_code == "qup")

kruskal.test(fr ~ site, data = vet) # p<0.001
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  fr by site
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 64.431, df = 9, p-value = 1.861e-10
kruskal.test(fr ~ site, data = vir) # p<0.001
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  fr by site
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 70.913, df = 11, p-value = 8.19e-11
kruskal.test(br ~ site, data = vet) # p>0.5 (p=0.63)
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  br by site
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 7.1086, df = 9, p-value = 0.6258
kruskal.test(br ~ site, data = vir) # p>0.5 (p=0.55)
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  br by site
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 9.772, df = 11, p-value = 0.551
kruskal.test(g_frac ~ site, data = vet) # p<0.001
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  g_frac by site
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 61.308, df = 9, p-value = 7.498e-10
kruskal.test(g_frac ~ site, data = vir) # p<0.001
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  g_frac by site
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 77.735, df = 11, p-value = 4.038e-12
kruskal.test(for_bites ~ site, data = vet) # p<0.001
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  for_bites by site
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 48.983, df = 9, p-value = 1.672e-07
kruskal.test(for_bites ~ site, data = vir) # p<0.001
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  for_bites by site
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 63.447, df = 11, p-value = 2.108e-09

Supplement

Predator gape size

From Mumby et al.: Grouper E. striatus, gape width (G): G = -0.5998 + (0.167 TL)

g30_mum <- -0.5998 + (0.167 * 30) # 4
g40_mum <- -0.5998 + (0.167 * 40) # 6

From Goatley & Bellwood: Horizontal gape: G = -0.002 * SL + 6.421

g30_goat <- -0.002 * 30 + 6.421
g40_goat <- -0.002 * 40 + 6.421

Dorsoventral height (Rakitin & Kramer 1996): S. viride: 15cm FL > 4.5cm body depth S. vetula: 15cm FL > 4.5cm body depth
